ISSUE #1 — XSS Risk via innerHTML
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Line:       226
Severity:   HIGH
Code:       p.innerHTML = '<span class="ig-heading-blue">Heading to the airport? </span> Book a cab now ';

Detail:     Using innerHTML introduces an XSS attack vector. Although current
            content is static, this pattern is inherently unsafe — any future
            change involving dynamic data (e.g., user name, city) will create
            an exploitable vulnerability. Also triggers full HTML re-parsing.

Solution:   Use safe DOM APIs:

            p.textContent = '';
            var span = document.createElement('span');
            span.className = 'ig-heading-blue';
            span.textContent = 'Heading to the airport? ';
            p.appendChild(span);
            p.appendChild(document.createTextNode(' Book a cab now '));

