ISSUE #2 — Unbounded Polling Fallback (Resource Leak)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Line:       276-278
Severity:   HIGH
Code:       var pollTimer = setInterval(function() {
                if (mount()) clearInterval(pollTimer);
            }, 500);

Detail:     If MutationObserver is unavailable and `mount()` never succeeds
            (container never appears), this interval runs forever at 500ms
            without any cap. On mobile devices this is especially harmful —
            drains battery and keeps the JavaScript thread busy.

Solution:   Add a maximum retry limit:

            var pollCount = 0;
            var MAX_POLLS = 40; // 20 seconds max
            var pollTimer = setInterval(function() {
                pollCount++;
                if (mount() || pollCount >= MAX_POLLS) clearInterval(pollTimer);
            }, 500);

