ISSUE #3 — Resize Handler Not Debounced (Causes Jank on Mobile)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Line:       299-305
Severity:   HIGH
Code:       function onResize() {
                if (!isMobile() && _mounted) {
                    _mounted = false;
                    stopCarousel();
                    removeInjectedNodes();
                } else if (isMobile() && !_mounted) {
                    mount();
                }
            }
            ...
            window.addEventListener("resize", onResize);

Detail:     On mobile, the resize event fires rapidly during orientation changes,
            virtual keyboard open/close, and address bar show/hide. Each firing
            calls isMobile() + potentially mount()/removeInjectedNodes() which
            triggers DOM reads and writes — causing layout thrashing and visible
            jank. The Desktop version debounces this; the Mobile version does not.

Solution:   Debounce the handler:

            var _resizeTimer = null;
            function onResizeDebounced() {
                clearTimeout(_resizeTimer);
                _resizeTimer = setTimeout(onResize, 150);
            }
            window.addEventListener("resize", onResizeDebounced);

            Also clear the timer in the destroy function.

