ISSUE #4 — STYLE_ID Collision with Desktop Version
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Line:       4
Severity:   HIGH
Code:       var STYLE_ID = "ig-cab-injector-styles";

Detail:     Both the Desktop and Mobile scripts use the IDENTICAL style ID
            "ig-cab-injector-styles". If both scripts are loaded on the same
            page (common for responsive sites), only ONE style block is injected
            (due to the `if (document.getElementById(STYLE_ID)) return` guard).
            The second script's styles are silently lost, causing broken layout
            on either mobile or desktop depending on load order.

Solution:   Use unique IDs per variant:

            var STYLE_ID = "ig-cab-injector-styles-mobile";

            Or consolidate both scripts into one with responsive CSS.

