ISSUE #5 — Overly Broad MutationObserver (Performance on Mobile)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Line:       280-286
Severity:   HIGH
Code:       _observer = new MutationObserver(function() {
                if (!_mounted) mount();
            });
            _observer.observe(document.body || document.documentElement, {
                childList: true,
                subtree: true
            });

Detail:     Observing the entire DOM tree fires the callback on EVERY mutation.
            On mobile SPAs with analytics, lazy loading, and ads, this fires
            hundreds of times per second. Each invocation calls mount() which
            runs querySelector — causing battery drain and potential frame drops
            on lower-end mobile devices.

Solution:   1. Disconnect observer after successful mount:

            _observer = new MutationObserver(function() {
                if (!_mounted && mount()) {
                    _observer.disconnect();
                    _observer = null;
                }
            });

            2. Or narrow the observe scope to a known ancestor.
            3. Or debounce the callback with requestAnimationFrame:

            var _rafPending = false;
            _observer = new MutationObserver(function() {
                if (_rafPending || _mounted) return;
                _rafPending = true;
                requestAnimationFrame(function() {
                    _rafPending = false;
                    if (!_mounted) mount();
                });
            });

