ISSUE #6 — No Double-Initialization Guard (Duplicate Timers)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Line:       318 (init function), 8 (CAROUSEL_INTERVAL), 9 (HEARTBEAT_MS)
Severity:   HIGH
Code:       function init() { ... mount(); startObserver(); startHeartbeat(); }

Detail:     If this IIFE is injected more than once (tag managers, SPA
            re-renders, or A/B testing tools re-evaluating), multiple heartbeat
            intervals and carousel timers stack up. Each instance creates its
            own closure with separate `_heartbeat` / `_carouselTimer` variables,
            so the internal guards (`if (_heartbeat) return`) don't protect
            against cross-instance duplication.

Solution:   Add a global sentinel at the top of the IIFE:

            if (window.__igCabMobileActive) return;
            window.__igCabMobileActive = true;

            Clear it in destroy:
            window.__igCabMobileActive = false;

