ISSUE #7 — Carousel Timer Leak on Page Unload
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Line:       115-120
Severity:   MEDIUM-HIGH
Code:       function startCarousel() {
                stopCarousel();
                _carouselTimer = setInterval(function() {
                    goToSlide((_carouselIndex + 1) % PERKS.length);
                }, CAROUSEL_INTERVAL);
            }

Detail:     The carousel auto-advance timer runs every 3 seconds indefinitely.
            While visibilitychange stops it when the tab is hidden, there is no
            cleanup on `beforeunload` or `pagehide`. In bfcache-enabled browsers,
            the page can be restored with stale timers. Additionally, if the DOM
            elements are removed by an SPA navigation but the heartbeat hasn't
            fired yet, goToSlide() will call getElementById on removed elements.

Solution:   Add a null-check in the carousel callback:

            _carouselTimer = setInterval(function() {
                var inner = document.getElementById("ig-carousel-slides-inner");
                if (!inner) { stopCarousel(); return; }
                goToSlide((_carouselIndex + 1) % PERKS.length);
            }, CAROUSEL_INTERVAL);

            Also add pagehide cleanup:
            window.addEventListener("pagehide", stopCarousel);

