ISSUE #8 — Global Namespace Pollution
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Line:       307
Severity:   MEDIUM-HIGH
Code:       window.__igCabInjectorDestroy = function() { ... };

Detail:     Same global name as the Desktop version. If both scripts are loaded,
            the Mobile version's destroy overwrites the Desktop one (or vice
            versa). Calling destroy will only clean up one variant, leaving the
            other's intervals/observers active — a memory/resource leak.

Solution:   Use variant-specific names:

            window.__igCabMobileDestroy = function() { ... };

            Or namespace properly:
            window.IndiGo = window.IndiGo || {};
            window.IndiGo.cabMobile = { destroy: function() { ... } };

