ISSUE #9 — External Resources Without Error Handling
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Lines:      22-32, 38-39
Severity:   MEDIUM-HIGH
Code:       iconUrl: "https://www.goindigo.in/content/dam/..."
            var CHECK_ICON = "https://www.goindigo.in/content/dam/..."
            var CIRCLE_ICON = "https://www.goindigo.in/content/dam/..."

Detail:     Images are loaded from an external CDN with no `onerror` fallback.
            On mobile with unreliable connections, broken images degrade the UI
            significantly. Additionally, no Subresource Integrity (SRI) is
            possible for images, but missing alt-text fallback and visual
            handling is a UX concern.

Solution:   Add error handlers to all dynamically created images:

            img.onerror = function() {
                this.style.display = 'none';
                // or swap to a data-uri fallback
            };

