ISSUE #10 — Heartbeat Does Not Re-mount After Container Reappears
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Lines:      256-259
Severity:   MEDIUM
Code:       if (!_mounted) return;
            var container = document.querySelector(CONTAINER_SEL);
            if (!container) {
                _mounted = false;
                stopCarousel();
                return;
            }

Detail:     When the container disappears (SPA navigation), heartbeat sets
            `_mounted = false` and returns. On subsequent ticks, the early
            `if (!_mounted) return;` (line 256) exits immediately without
            attempting to re-mount — even if the container has reappeared.
            The observer may also miss this if it was disconnected or if
            the mutation happened between checks.

Solution:   Change logic to attempt mount when not mounted:

            if (!_mounted) { mount(); return; }

